    <stitle>TRW MANUAL STEERING GEAR - REPAIR - ROLLERSHAFT AND WORM SHAFT SEALS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ROLLERSHAFT AND WORM SHAFT SEALS</title>
        <para>It is recommended that seals be replaced with new seals if gear is disassembled. Assemble lubricated seals
            into counterbore with longest lip facing into gear. Use a mandrel of a size to contact all around seal case.
            Drive in seals to firmly contact bottom of counterbore.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Seal surface on worm shaft may be lightly polished with fine abrasive cloth to provide good
                    sealing surface.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
